Vuetify v-alert.description: The v-alert component is used to convey important information to the user through the use contextual types icons and color. These default types come in in 4 variations: success, info, warning, and error. Default icons are assigned which help represent different actions each type portrays. Many parts of an alert such as border, icon, and color can also be customized to fit almost any situation.

Vuetify v-app.description: The v-app component is REQUIRED for all applications. This is the mount point for many of Vuetify's components and functionality and ensures that. It propagates the default application variant (dark/light) to children components and also ensures proper cross-browser support for certain click events in browsers like Safari and should only be used within your application ONCE.

Vuetify v-app-bar.description: The v-app-bar component is pivotal to any graphical user interface (GUI), as it generally is the primary source of site navigation. The app-bar component works great in conjunction with a v-navigation-drawer for providing site navigation in your application.

Vuetify v-avatar.description: The v-avatar component is typically used to display circular user profile pictures. This component will allow you to dynamically size and add a border radius of responsive images, icons, and text. A tile variation is available for displaying an avatar without border radius.

Vuetify v-badge.description: The v-badge component superscripts or subscripts an avatar-like icon or text onto content to highlight information to a user or to just draw attention to a specific element. Content within the badge usually contains numbers or icons.

Vuetify v-banner.description: The v-banner component is used as middle-interruptive message to user with 1-2 actions. It comes in 2 variations, single-line and multi-line (implicit). These can have icons which you can use with your message and actions.

Vuetify v-bottom-navigation.description: The v-bottom-navigation is an alternative to the sidebar. It is primarily used on mobile and comes in two variants, icons and text, and shift.

Vuetify v-bottom-sheet.description: The bottom sheet is a modified v-dialog that slides from the bottom of the screen, similar to a v-bottom-navigation. Whereas a bottom navigation component is for buttons and specific application level actions, a bottom sheet can contain anything.

Vuetify v-breadcrumbs.description: The v-breadcrumbs component is a navigational helper for pages. It can accept a Material Icons icon or text characters as a divider. An array of objects can be passed to the items property of the component. Additionally, a scoped slot exists for more control of the breadcrumbs, either utilizing v-breadcrumbs-item or other custom markup.

Vuetify v-btn.description: The v-btn component replaces the standard html button with a material design theme and a multitude of options. Any color helper class can be used to alter the background or text color.

Vuetify v-btn icon.description: The v-btn component replaces the standard html button with a material design theme and a multitude of options. Any color helper class can be used to alter the background or text color.

Vuetify v-btn with color.description: The v-btn component replaces the standard html button with a material design theme and a multitude of options. Any color helper class can be used to alter the background or text color.

Vuetify v-calendar.description: The v-calendar component is used to display information in a daily, weekly, or monthly view. The daily view has slots for all day or timed elements, and the weekly and monthly view has a slot for each day. Optionally you can pass in an array of events and they will be rendered over the appropriate days and times.

Vuetify v-card.description: The v-card component is a versatile component that can be used for anything from a panel to a static image. The card component has numerous helper components to make markup as easy as possible. Components that have no listed options use Vue's functional component option for faster rendering and serve as markup sugar to make building easier.

Vuetify v-card-actions.description: The container used for placing actions for a card, such as v-btn or v-menu. Also applies special margin to buttons so that they properly line up with other card content areas.

Vuetify v-card-text.description: Primarily used for text content in a card. Applies padding for text, reduces its font-size to .875rem and changes its color to grey.

Vuetify v-card-title.description: Provides a default font-size and padding for card titles. Font-size can be overwritten with typography classes, (/styles/typography).

Vuetify v-carousel.description: The v-carousel component is used to display large numbers of visual content on a rotating timer.

Vuetify v-chip.description: The v-chip component is used to convey small pieces of information. Using the close property, the chip becomes interactive, allowing user interaction. This component is used by the v-chip-group for advanced selection options.

Vuetify v-chip-group.description: The v-chip-group supercharges the v-chip component by providing groupable functionality. It is used for creating groups of selections using chips.

Vuetify v-responsive.description: The v-responsive component can be used to fix any section to a specific aspect ratio

Vuetify v-speed-dial.description: The v-btn component can be used as a Floating action button. This provides an application a main point of action. Combined with the v-speed-dial component, you can create a diverse set of functions available for your users.

Vuetify v-system-bar.description: The v-system-bar component can be used for displaying some statuses to user. It looks like Android system bar and can contain icons, spacers and some amount of text.

Vuetify v-toolbar.description: The v-toolbar component is pivotal to any gui, as it generally is the primary source of site navigation. The toolbar component works great in conjunction with v-navigation-drawer and v-card.

Vuetify :active.sync.description: Holds the value of the currently active button. If the button has no value supplied, its index will be used instead. This prop supports the .sync modifier.

Vuetify :aspectRatio.description: Sets a base aspect ratio, calculated as width/height. This will only set a minimum height, the component can still grow if it has a lot of content.

Vuetify Calendar type.description: A string which is one of month, week, day, 4day, custom-weekly, and custom-daily. The custom types look at the start and end dates passed to the component as opposed to the value.

Vuetify absolute.description: Applies position: absolute to the component.

Vuetify activator.description: Designate a custom activator when the activator slot is not used. String can be any valid querySelector and Object can be any valid Node.

Vuetify active-class.description: Class bound when component is active. warning Depending upon the component, this could cause side effects. If you need to add a custom class on top of a default, just do active-class="default-class your-class". For example in v-bottom-navigation The class applied to a v-btn when activated Or v-breadcrumbs-item Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active. You can find more information about the active-class prop on the vue-router documentation.

Vuetify align-content-space-around.description: Align content to the space around.

Vuetify align-content-space-between.description: Align content to the space between.

Vuetify alt.description: Alternate text for screen readers. Leave empty for decorative images

Vuetify app.description: Designates the component as part of the application layout. Used for dynamically adjusting content sizing. Components using this prop should reside outside of v-content component to function properly. You can more information about layouts on the application page.

Vuetify append.description: Setting append prop always appends the relative path to the current path. You can find more information about the append prop on the vue-router documentation.

Vuetify aspect-ratio.description: Calculated as width/height, so for a 1920x1080px image this will be 1.7778. Will be calculated automatically if omitted

Vuetify attach.description: Specifies which DOM element that this component should detach to.String can be any valid querySelector and Object can be any valid Node. This will attach to the root v-app component by default.

Vuetify background-color.description: Changes the background-color for the component.

Vuetify block.description: Expands the button to 100% of available space

Vuetify border.description: Puts a border on the alert. Accepts top | right | bottom | left.

Vuetify bottom.description: Aligns the component towards the bottom.

Vuetify card.description: Inherits border radius when used within v-card

Vuetify clipped-left.description: Designates that the application's v-navigation-drawer that is positioned on the left is below the app-bar.

Vuetify clipped-right.description: Designates that the application's v-navigation-drawer that is positioned on the right is below the app-bar.

Vuetify close-icon.description: Change the default icon used for close chips

Vuetify close-label.description: Text used for aria-label on dismissible alerts. Can also be customizing globally in Internationalization.

Vuetify collapse.description: Puts the toolbar into a collapsed state reducing its maximum width.

Vuetify collapse-on-scroll.description: Puts the app-bar into a collapsed state when scrolling.

Vuetify color.description: Applies specified color to the control - it can be the name of material color (for example success or purple) or css color (#033 or rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5)). You can find list of built in classes on the colors page.

Vuetify colored-border.description: Applies the defined color to the alert's border.

Vuetify content-class.description: Applies a custom class to the detached element. This is useful because the content is moved to the beginning of the v-app component (unless the attach prop is provided) and is not targettable by classes passed directly on the component.

Vuetify continuous.description: If true, window will 'wrap around' from the last item to the first, and from the first item to the last

Vuetify cycle.description: Determines if the carousel should cycle through images.

Vuetify dark.description: Applies the dark theme variant to the component. You can find more information on the Material Design documentation for dark themes.

Vuetify day-format.description: Formats day of the month string that appears in a day to a specified locale

Vuetify dense.description: Hides the alert icon and decreases component's height OR Reduces the height of the toolbar content to 48px (96px when using the prominent prop).

Vuetify direction.description: Direction in which speed-dial content will show. Possible values are top, bottom, left, right.

Vuetify disabled.description: Route item is disabled or Disables the ability to open the component OR in v-breadcrumbs-item Removes the ability to click or target the component. In v-chip Disables the chip, making it un-selectable

Vuetify dismissible.description: Adds a close icon that can hide the alert.

Vuetify display.description: Specify to display an element as flex/inline-flex/block etc. Syntax is d-{type}. For example d-flex.

Vuetify divider.description: Specifies the dividing character between items.

Vuetify eager.description: Will force the components content to render on mounted. This is useful if you have content that will not be rendered in the DOM that you want crawled for SEO.

Vuetify elevation.description: Designates an elevation applied to the component between 0 and 24. You can find more information on the elevation page.

Vuetify end.description: The ending date on the calendar (inclusive) in the format of YYYY-MM-DD. This may be ignored depending on the type of the calendar.

Vuetify event-color.description: A background color for all events or a function which accepts an event object passed to the calendar to return a color.

Vuetify event-end.description: Set property of event's end timestamp.

Vuetify event-height.description: The height of an event in pixels in the month view and at the top of the day views.

Vuetify event-more.description: Whether the more 'button' is displayed on a calendar with too many events in a given day. It will say something like '5 more' and when clicked generates a click:more event.

Vuetify event-more-text.description: The text to display in the more 'button' given the number of hidden events.

Vuetify event-name.description: Set property of event's displayed name, or a function which accepts an event object passed to the calendar as the first argument and a flag signalling whether the name is for a timed event (true) or an event over a day.

Vuetify event-overlap-threshold.description: A value in minutes that's used to determine whether two timed events should be placed in column beside each other or should be treated as slightly overlapping events.

Vuetify event-start.description: Set property of event's start timestamp.

Vuetify event-text-color.description: A text color for all events or a function which accepts an event object passed to the calendar to return a color.

Vuetify events.description: An array of event objects with a property for a start timestamp and optionally a name and end timestamp. If an end timestamp is not given, the value of start will be used. If no name is given, you must provide an implementation for the event slot.

Vuetify exact.description: Exactly match the link. Without this, '/' will match every route. You can find more information about the exact prop on the vue-router documentation.

Vuetify exact-active-class.description: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact match. You can find more information about the exact-active-class prop on the vue-router documentation.

Vuetify extended.description: Use this prop to increase the height of the toolbar without using the extension slot for adding content. May be used in conjunction with the extension-height prop, and any of the other props that affect the height of the toolbar, e.g. prominent, dense, etc., WITH THE EXCEPTION of height.

Vuetify extension-height.description: Specify an explicit height for the extension slot.

Vuetify fab.description: Designates the button as a floating-action-button - round.

Vuetify fade-img-on-scroll.description: When using the src prop or img scoped slot, will fade the image when scrolling.

Vuetify fill-height.description: Make sure that col element height is filled with parent and child. Important for Safari/Firefox if children is column element.

Vuetify filter.description: Displays a selection icon when selected

Vuetify filter-icon.description: Change the default icon used for filter chips

Vuetify first-interval.description: The first interval to display in the day view. If intervalMinutes is set to 60 and this is set to 9 the first time in the view is 9am.

Vuetify fixed.description: Applies position: fixed to the component.

Vuetify flat.description: Removes the button background color or Removes the card's elevation or Removes the toolbar's box-shadow.

Vuetify floating.description: Applies display: inline-flex to the component.

Vuetify full-width.description: Forces the dialog to expand 100% of available width.

Vuetify gradient.description: Overlays a gradient onto the image. Only supports linear-gradient syntax, anything else should be done with classes (see examples)

Vuetify grid-list.description: Sets the gutter between grid list items ranging from 2px to 24px

Vuetify grow.description: Force v-btns to take up all available space.

Vuetify height.description: Sets the height for the component AND in v-toolbar overrides the heights imposed by other props, e.g. prominent, dense, extended, etc..

Vuetify hide-header.description: If the header at the top of the day view should be visible.

Vuetify hide-on-scroll.description: Hides the app-bar when scrolling. Will still show the extension slot OR in v-bottom-navigation Will transition the navigation off screen when scrolling up.

Vuetify hide-overlay.description: Hides the display of the overlay.

Vuetify horizontal.description: Uses an alternative horizontal styling for v-btn.

Vuetify hover.description: Will apply an elevation of 4dp when hovered (default 2dp). You can find more information on the elevation page.

Vuetify href.description: Designates the component as anchor and applies the href attribute.

Vuetify icon.description: Designates a specific icon OR in v-btn Designates the button as icon - round and flat

Vuetify icon button.description: Designates the button as icon - round and flat

Vuetify id.description: Sets the DOM id on the component.

Vuetify img.description: Specifies an image background for the card. For more advanced implementations, it is recommended that you use the v-img component.

Vuetify input-value.description: Controls whether the component is visible or hidden. Supports the .sync modifier. In v-btn Controls the button's active state. In v-chip Designates whether the component is selected, highlighting the chip.

Vuetify inset.description: Reduces the sheet content maximum width to 70%.

Vuetify internal-activator.description: Designates whether the supplied activator prop is inside the component.

Vuetify interval.description: The duration between image cycles. Requires the cycle prop.

Vuetify interval-count.description: The number of intervals to display in the day view.

Vuetify interval-format.description: Formats time of day string that appears in the interval gutter of the day and week view to specified locale

Vuetify interval-height.description: The height of an interval in pixels in the day view.

Vuetify interval-minutes.description: The number of minutes the intervals are in the day view. A common interval is 60 minutes so the intervals are an hour.

Vuetify interval-style.description: Returns CSS styling to apply to the interval.

Vuetify inverted-scroll.description: Will slide out of view when scrolling down and back into view when scrolling up OR Hides the app-bar when scrolling down and displays it when scrolling up.

Vuetify items.description: An array of objects for each breadcrumb. See v-breadcrumbs-item API section for all object properties. Use text property for the breadcrumb text.

Vuetify justify-space-around.description: Justify content to the space around.

Vuetify justify-space-between.description: Justify content to the space between.

Vuetify large.description: Increase the font-size of the breadcrumb item text to 16px (14px default) OR in v-btn Makes the component large.

Vuetify lazy.description: Conditionally renders content on mounted. Will only render content if activated

Vuetify lazy-src.description: Something to show while waiting for the main image to load, typically a small base64-encoded thumbnail. Has a slight blur filter applied. Use vuetify-loader to generate automatically

Vuetify left.description: Designates that the avatar is on the left side of a component. This is hooked into by components such as v-chip and v-btn. OR Aligns the component towards the left. This should be used with the absolute or fixed props.

Vuetify light.description: Applies the light theme variant to the component.

Vuetify link.description: Designates that the component is a link. This is automatic when using the href or to prop.

Vuetify loader-height.description: Specifies the height of the loader

Vuetify loading.description: Displays linear progress bar. Can either be a String which specifies which color is applied to the progress bar (any material color or theme color - primary, secondary, success, info, warning, error) or a Boolean which uses the component color (set by color prop - if it's supported by the component) or the primary color

Vuetify mandatory.description: Forces a value to always be selected (if available).

Vuetify margin.description: The helper classes apply margin to an element ranging from 0 to 5. Each size increment was designed to align with common Material Design spacings. These classes can be applied using the following format m{direction}-{size}.

Vuetify max.description: Sets a maximum number of selections that can be made.

Vuetify max-days.description: The maximum number of days to display in the custom calendar if an end day is not set.

Vuetify max-height.description: Sets the maximum height for the component.

Vuetify max-width.description: Sets the maximum width for the component.

Vuetify min-height.description: Sets the minimum height for the component.

Vuetify min-weeks.description: The minimum number of weeks to display in the month or week view.

Vuetify min-width.description: Sets the minimum width for the component.

Vuetify mobile-break-point.description: Sets the designated mobile breakpoint for the component. This will apply alternate styles for mobile devices.

Vuetify mode.description: Sets the transition mode (does not apply to transition-group). You can find more information on the Vue documentation for transition modes.

Vuetify month-format.description: Formats month string that appears in a day to specified locale

Vuetify multiple.description: Allow multiple selections. The value prop must be an array.

Vuetify next-icon.description: Icon used for the 'next' button if show-arrows is true

Vuetify no-click-animation.description: Disables the bounce effect when clicking outside of a v-dialog's content when using the persistent prop.

Vuetify now.description: Override the day & time which is considered now. This is in the format of YYYY-MM-DD hh:mm:ss. The calendar is styled according to now.

Vuetify nuxt.description: Specifies the link is a nuxt-link. For use with the nuxt framework.

Vuetify open-on-hover.description: Designates whether component should activate when its activator is hovered. In v-speed-dial Opens speed-dial on hover

Vuetify origin.description: Sets the transition origin on the element. You can find more information on the MDN documentation for transition origin.

Vuetify outline.description: Button or Alert will have an outline

Vuetify outlined.description: Removes card elevation shadow and adds a thin border. In v-chip Removes background and applies border and text color

Vuetify overflow.description: Set the overflow for an element with overflow-{axis}-hidden or simply overflow-hidden.

Vuetify overlap.description: Overlaps the slotted content on top of the component.

Vuetify padding.description: The helper classes apply padding to an element ranging from 0 to 5. Each size increment was designed to align with common Material Design spacings. These classes can be applied using the following format p{direction}-{size}.

Vuetify persistent.description: Clicking outside of the element will not deactivate it.

Vuetify position.description: Overrides the default to change which parts get cropped off. Uses the same syntax as background-position

Vuetify prev-icon.description: Icon used for the 'prev' button if show-arrows is true

Vuetify progress.description: Displays a carousel progress bar. Requires the cycle prop and interval.

Vuetify progress-color.description: Applies specified color to progress bar.

Vuetify prominent.description: Displays a larger vertically centered icon to draw more attention OR Increases the height of the toolbar content to 128px.

Vuetify raised.description: Specifies a higher default elevation (8dp). You can find more information on the elevation page.

Vuetify replace.description: Setting replace prop will call router.replace() instead of router.push() when clicked, so the navigation will not leave a history record. You can find more information about the replace prop on the vue-router documentation.

Vuetify reverse.description: Sets flex direction to row or (in carousels) manually set the window to use the reverseTransition

Vuetify right.description: Designates that the avatar is on the right side of a component. This is hooked into by components such as v-chip and v-btn. OR Aligns the component towards the right. This should be used with the absolute or fixed props.

Vuetify round.description: Button will be round on the sides

Vuetify rounded.description: Applies a large border radius on the buttons.

Vuetify scroll-off-screen.description: Will transition the toolbar and extension off screen when scrolling down OR Hides the app-bar when scrolling. Will NOT show the extension slot.

Vuetify scroll-target.description: Assign the scroll target for scroll-off-screen OR in v-app-bar designates the element to target for scrolling events. Uses window by default.

Vuetify scroll-threshold.description: The amount of scroll distance down before the toolbar uses scroll-off-screen OR in v-app-bar the amount of scroll distance down before hide-on-scroll activates.

Vuetify scroll-toolbar-off-screen.description: Will transition the toolbar off screen when scrolling down

Vuetify scrollable.description: When set to true, expects a v-card and a v-card-text component with a designated height. For more information, check out the scrollabe example.

Vuetify shaped.description: Provides an alternative active style for v-list-item.

Vuetify shift.description: Hides text of v-btns when they are not active.

Vuetify short.description: Reduce the height of the toolbar content to 56px (112px when using the prominent prop).

Vuetify short-intervals.description: If true, the intervals in the day view will be 9 AM as opposed to 09:00 AM

Vuetify short-months.description: Whether the short versions of a month should be used (Jan vs January).

Vuetify short-weekdays.description: Whether the short versions of a weekday should be used (Mon vs Monday).

Vuetify show-arrows-on-hover.description: Display the 'next'and 'prev' buttons on hover. show-arrows MUST ALSO be set.

Vuetify show-interval-label.description: Checks if a given day and time should be displayed in the interval gutter of the day view.

Vuetify show-interval-on-first.description: Checks if a given day and time should be displayed in the interval gutter of the day view.

Vuetify show-month-on-first.description: Whether the name of the month should be displayed on the first day of the month.

Vuetify shrink-on-scroll.description: Shrinks a prominent toolbar to a dense or short (default) one when scrolling.

Vuetify single-line.description: Forces the banner onto a single line.

Vuetify size.description: Sets the height and width of the component.

Vuetify sizes.description: For use with srcset, see MDN

Vuetify slot-icon.description: The slot used for the icon's content.

Vuetify src.description: Specifies a v-img as the component's background.

Vuetify srcset.description: A set of alternate images to use based on device size.

Vuetify start.description: The starting date on the calendar (inclusive) in the format of YYYY-MM-DD. This may be ignored depending on the type of the calendar.

Vuetify sticky.description: Applies position: sticky to the component (Evergreen browsers only). You can find more information on the MDN documentation for sticky position.

Vuetify tabs.description: Will set an explicit 42px height for extension. Useful when default v-tabs are used in the extended slot. If you have a custom height v-tab, you should specify a height with extensionHeight.

Vuetify tag.description: Specify a custom tag used on the root element.

Vuetify target.description: Designates the target attribute. This should only be applied when using the href prop.

Vuetify text.description: Applies the defined color to text and a low opacity background of the same. In v-btn Makes the background transparent.

Vuetify text-color.description: Applies a specified color to the control text

Vuetify to.description: Denotes the target route of the link. You can find more information about the to prop on the vue-router documentation.

Vuetify top.description: Aligns the content towards the top.

Vuetify touch.description: Provide a custom left and right function when swiped left or right

Vuetify transition.description: Sets the component transition. Can be one of the built in transitions or one your own.

Vuetify type.description: Specify a success, info, warning or error alert. Uses the contextual color and a pre-defined icon. Or Set the button's type attribute

Vuetify value.description: Controls whether the component is visible or hidden OR in v-bottom-navigation Holds the value of the currently active v-btn. If the button has no value supplied, its index will be used instead. In v-btn The value used when the component is selected in a group.

Vuetify value calendar.description: A date in the format of YYYY-MM-DD which determines what span of time for the calendar.

Vuetify vertical.description: Uses a vertical transition when changing windows

Vuetify weekday-format.description: Formats day of the week string that appears in the header to specified locale

Vuetify weekdays.description: Specifies which days of the week to display. To display Monday through Friday only, a value of [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] can be used. To display a week starting on Monday a value of [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 0] can be used.

Vuetify width.description: Sets the width for the component.

Vuetify window.description: Increases the system bar height to 32px (24px default).

Vuetify wrap.description: Allows children to wrap within the container if the elements use more than 100%.
